14) Bron putting on a clinic at the TD Garden. (2010)

The game was basically over after the 1st quarter as Lebron made a statement early with 21 first quarter points. Handed the C’s a 29 pt loss, which was their worst home playoff loss at the time.

38 PTS/8 RBS/7ASTS/63%FG/+30 https://t.co/eIjtA5upG0

13) 0.9 Seconds Left. (2009)

Down 0-1 trying to avoid an 0-2 hole, Lebron delivers a clutch performance. He hit arguably his greatest buzzer ever & one of the greatest playoff buzzer beaters ever hitting a 3 down 2 to ORL.

35 PTS/5 AST/52% FG/10 FTM https://t.co/Ei8WAQEu5W

12) Bron’s Southern Cooking. (2009)

Up 2-0 on the Hawks, Lebron put the nail in the coffin & torched Atlanta with a near triple 40 pt triple double to go up 3-0 in the series.

47 PTS/12 RBS/8 ASTS/5 3s/60%FG https://t.co/pHCAswS6vy

11) Lebron’s Double Nickel. (2009)

Lebron was cooking in Milwaukee, especially in the 3rd quarter where he scored 16 points in 2 minutes. He scored an overall 24 points in the 3rd quarter. Another masterpiece en route to winning his 1st MVP. ⬆️

55 PTS/9 ASTS/8 3PM/55% FG https://t.co/LPXJh6vs51
Nestor is getting hit a little now!!!

10) 50 Burger in the Big🍎 (2009)

Lebron with an all around dominant, clutch game at Madison Square Garden as he filled up the stat sheet with a near triple double. The NBA removed his last rebound.

52PTS/11ASTS/9RBS/16FTS/51%FG https://t.co/Ns8PJAI7oR

9) Legendary Game 7 Duel. (2008)

Lebron & the Cavs took the 1 seed Big 3 Celtics to a game 7. This led to one of the most iconic duels between Lebron & Pierce. Despite the Herculean effort from Lebron, CLE lost to the eventual champs.

45 PTS/6 ASTS/5 RBS/48% FG https://t.co/9xDYrfUiMD

8) Battle of the Best. (2008)

Another memorable duel between the two best players in the NBA, and Lebron won this round. Despite Kobe’s 33 points, Cavs prevailed behind’s Lebron’s great game, including 14 points in the 4th.

41 PTS/9 RBS/50% FG https://t.co/QL2rFBwkiX

7) Iconic. Generational. (2007)

Series tied 2-2. Facing the 1 seed DET, who beat CLE in 06.

Lebron does this:
• 48 PTS/9 RBS/7 ASTS/54%FG
• 25 straight points in 4th/OT
• 29 of the Cavs last 30 points
• 3 game-tying/go-ahead shots in final minute of 4th/OT
• Game Winner 👑 https://t.co/pj8x4HOmqp

6)“The Layup” (2006)

Series tied 2-2 trying to avoid going down 2-3 back to WAS, Lebron drops 45 points with an all time clutch performance. Down 1 in Overtime, Lebron scores the game winning layup to go up 3-2. Cavs closed the series out in 6.

45 PTS/7 RBS/6 ASTS/61% FG https://t.co/XfslI7Hn0n

4) Lebron outduels DWade in a legendary battle. (2006)

21 year old Lebron drops a near triple double vs the eventual champs Miami Heat. Dwade had 44 points. A legendary battle of titans decided in the final moments of the game.

47 PTS/12 RBS/9 ASTS/67% FG https://t.co/5zT60Payqu

3)🔥in the Rocky Mountains. (2006)

21 yr old Lebron on the 2nd night of a back to back cooked Utah. He dropped 50+ for the 3rd time in his young career as he had Utah’s bench amazed. When you have the Utah crowd cheering, you know it’s real.

51 PTS/8 ASTS/54% FG https://t.co/AFrGZXB0FW
